%N A395524 Decimal expansion of the mode of the distribution of distances between two points in two adjacent unit squares that share a common edge.
%C A395524 The smaller real root of 6*x^2 - 8*x + 3 - 8*sqrt(x^2-1) + 4*arccos(1/x) = 0.
%H A395524 Vangalur S. Alagar, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3212475">The Distribution of the Distance between Random Points</a>, Journal of Applied Probability, Vol. 13, No. 3 (1976), pp. 558-566. See p. 565, eq. (18).
%e A395524 1.039761666820869318880380641486869221803881823551613...
%t A395524 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[6*x^2 - 8*x + 3 - 8*Sqrt[x^2-1] + 4*ArcCos[1/x], {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A395524 (PARI) solve(x = 1, 3/2, 6*x^2 - 8*x + 3 - 8*sqrt(x^2-1) + 4*acos(1/x))
